Fig. 6E
) with strong, crenulate pars incisiva, stout lacinia mobilis with four denticles, setiferous lobe setulose and with seven simple setae, pars molaris stout, blunt, distally with delicate marginal teeth and plumose setae on posterior edge (
Fig. 6F
); palp of three articles, proximal article with one inner seta; second article 0.6 times the length of the whole palp, with five simple inner distal setae; third article as long as

